<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,248]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</emphasis>
The single specimen we examined is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1795" box="[865,1006,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africanus">
<emphasis box="[865,1006,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">H. africanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1077,1168,224,247]" country="Zambia" name="Western" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Western</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1225,1391,223,248]" country="South Africa" name="Northern Cape" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<collectingRegion box="[1225,1326,223,248]" country="Zambia" name="Northern" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Northern</collectingRegion>
Cape
</collectingRegion>
but the pronotum is more depressed anteriorly, the head and pronotum punctures are more subrugose and confluent, the head, pronotum and ventral setae are longer and distinctly golden. The mesosternum is illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1382,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="82.[151,250,1804,1826]" captionTargetBox="[195,1406,509,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@82.[151,1436,483,1782]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hycleus aridus: tegmenin ventral view (A); tegmen and aedeagus in lateral view (B); antenna (C); mesosternum (D).Hycleus cfr. africanus: mesosternum (E). Bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1151782/files/figure.png" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Fig. 16E</figureCitation>
. The elytral pattern and setation correspond to that of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Peringuey, 1909" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1909" box="[772,1108,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Decatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="africana" variety="insolita">
var. 
<emphasis box="[824,908,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">insolita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Peringuey" box="[919,1108,332,357]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" refString="Peringuey, L. (1909) Descriptive catalogue of the Coleoptera of South Africa Family Meloidae. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Africa, 1, 165 - 297, 4 pls." type="journal article" year="1909">Péringuey, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was considered as a possible distinct species by the 
<collectingRegion box="[501,566,367,392]" country="Tanzania" name="Kusini Unguja" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">South</collectingRegion>
African entomologist. The deeply examination of 
<typeStatus box="[1131,1190,368,392]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">types</typeStatus>
of both 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1795" box="[1283,1388,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africanus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1388,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">africanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Laporte, 1840" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1909" box="[151,283,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Decatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="africana" variety="insolita">
var. 
<emphasis box="[199,283,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">insolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is basic to the resolution of this taxonomic problem.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
